# Cline Rules - Amber Electric Dashboard

Project: Amber Electric Dashboard, a Flutter app that visualises a customer's
Amber Electric (Australia) electricity usage and prices.

## Commands
- `flutter pub get` - install/refresh dependencies.
- `flutter test` - run the test suite (aggregation logic + widget tests).
- `flutter analyze` - static analysis. Pre-existing SDK deprecation/info
  warnings are expected; treat any NEW error as a regression.

## Tests
- `test/bar_chart_test.dart` - `DataAggregator` aggregation tests covering
  both 30-minute and 5-minute billing scenarios. The 5-minute test asserts
  48 half-hour bars, each summing 6 x 1.0 kWh = 6.0.
- `test/widget_test.dart` - basic widget smoke test.

## Chart aggregation model (IMPORTANT)
- Graph bars are FIXED **half-hour buckets**: 2 bars/hour = 48 bars/day. This
  is intentional and must NOT be changed to one-bar-per-interval.
- 30-minute billing: one interval per bar.
- 5-minute billing: **6 five-minute intervals are summed into each half-hour
  bar** (value = sum of 6 x 5-min kWh or cost).
- In `lib/bar_chart.dart`, `graphPos` and `nowIndex` use
  `date.hour * 2 + date.minute ~/ 30` (half-hour width); the fill loop is
  bounded to `24 * (60 ~/ 30)` = 48 bars.
- Do NOT "fix" this to 288 bars for 5-minute data - that was tried and
  reverted because it produced wrong time ranges and values.
- The data fetch in `lib/main.dart` (`_getForecast`) correctly uses
  `60 ~/ intervalLength` periods/hour so enough 5-minute periods are fetched;
  keep that behaviour.

## Key constants (lib/bar_chart.dart)
- `meterInterval` = 30 (default meter interval and the half-hour bar width).
- `daily` = daily supply charge, spread across bars.
- `intervalLength` (lib/main.dart) comes from the selected site and defaults
  to `meterInterval`; 5-minute sites report 5.

## Versioning
- `pubspec.yaml`: `version: x.y.z+build` (e.g. `0.5.2+41`).
- Minor version bumps and a sequentially increasing build number follow the
  existing commit history convention.

## Deployment
- No local deploy script. CI is Codemagic. **Push to `origin/master`** to
  trigger the build/deploy (web, Android, iOS). There is no `codemagic.yaml`
  in the repo - it is configured via the Codemagic dashboard.

## Gotchas
- Test runs can fail with "Flutter failed to delete a directory at
  build\unit_test_assets" (a locked build dir). Fix by deleting the build
  folder (`Remove-Item -Recurse -Force build`) and re-running `flutter test`.
- Repo files are **CRLF**. Multi-line edits via the editor tool using `\n`
  fail to match; prefer single-line edits or include `\r\n`.
- When pushing, a plain `git push origin master` can falsely print
  "Everything up-to-date" even when the commit is still local. Use
  `git push origin master --verbose` to force a real push, then confirm
  with `git log origin/master` (it must show your new commit on top).
- `lib/utils.dart` `darken`/`lighten` still use the deprecated
  `Color.red/green/blue/alpha` getters; left intentionally (SDK deprecation,
  not a logic bug).
